About R.V. College of Engineering
Established: 1963
Accredited / Approved: AICTE / NBA
Affiliated: Visvesvaraya Technological University
R.V. College of Engineering was set up in the year 1963 spread over 51.4 acres on the banks of the Vrishabhavati River in Bangalore. The autonomous institution is affiliated to Visvesvarya Technological University and is approved by NBA, AICTE, New Delhi.
R.V. College of Engineering was ranked 49th engineering colleges in India by the National Institutional Ranking Framework in the year 2017.
Call: ‎09742814850 Ranjeet Singh For BE| B.TECH admission guidance in RV College of Engineering Bangalore
More Details: http://admissionblock.com/
R.V. College of Engineering motivates students in organizing events like Genesis: intercollegiate festival, React: Chemical Engineering fest, Infinity: Information Science and Engineering fest, Impulse: Electronics and Communication Engineering fest, Helix: Biotechnology fest, Vortex: Mechanical Engineering fest, Vantage: Instrumentation Technology fest and Connect: Telecommunication Engineering fest.
R.V. College of Engineering enables vast exhibition of talents in the campus out of which few notable alumni who excellent in their field are Anil Kumble, the former coach and captain of the Indian Cricket Team and Chetan Baboor, Table tennis player.
